<div align="center"><table width="50%" border="0"><tr><td valign="top"><b>Links</b></td></tr><tr><td><ul>Notes from the Bee Lab:  This species may be a specialist on Nothoscordum bivalve and perhaps Nothoscordum gracile...this remains to be completely documented and we encourage people to continue collecting off of this plant group.  Jack Neff notes that in TX he does NOT collect this species on Nothoscordum species despite the commonness of that plant.  


